29/06/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- In a recent interview for <I>Romania Actualitati</I>, NATO Secretary General George Robertson said Romania has achieved remarkable progress in army reforms, but added that more must be done to meet NATO standards. 
Rompres reported his statement on Saturday (28 June). 
Robertson also said the government must continue to allocate 2 per cent of the country's GDP to defence spending. 
(Rompres - 28/06/03)
